19 (c) Credit Refundable. – If the credit allowed by this section exceeds the amount of tax
20 imposed by this Part for the taxable year reduced by the sum of all credits allowable, the Secretary
21 must refund the excess to the taxpayer. The refundable excess is governed by the provisions
22 governing a refund of an overpayment by the taxpayer of the tax imposed by this Part. In
23 computing the amount of tax against which multiple credits are allowed, nonrefundable credits
24 are subtracted before refundable credits.
25 "§ 105-153.13. Midlife healthcare business tax credit.
26 (a) Definitions. – The definitions in G.S. 105-153.12 and the following definitions apply
27 in this section:
28 (1) Eligible business. – A business with a physical presence in the State that has
29 out-of-pocket expenses.
30 (2) Out-of-pocket expenses. – As defined in G.S. 105-153.12 and paid by an
31 eligible business on behalf of a qualifying employee.
32 (3) Qualifying employee. – An individual employed (i) for consideration for at
33 least 35 hours a week and whose wages are subject to withholding under
34 Article 4A of Chapter 105 of the General Statutes and (ii) by an eligible
35 business.
36 (b) Credit. – A taxpayer who is an eligible business and has out-of-pocket expenses is
37 allowed a credit against the tax imposed by this Part equal to ten percent (10%) of the taxpayer's
38 total out-of-pocket expenses.
39 (c) Credit Refundable. – If the credit allowed by this section exceeds the amount of tax
40 imposed by this Part for the taxable year reduced by the sum of all credits allowable, the Secretary
41 must refund the excess to the taxpayer. The refundable excess is governed by the provisions
42 governing a refund of an overpayment by the taxpayer of the tax imposed by this Part. In
43 computing the amount of tax against which multiple credits are allowed, nonrefundable credits
44 are subtracted before refundable credits.
45 (d) Aggregate Limitation. – The total amount of credits allowed pursuant to this section
46 may not exceed in the aggregate five million dollars ($5,000,000) for all taxpayers for any one
47 calendar year.
48 (e) Application. – An eligible business seeking to claim a tax credit provided for under
49 this section shall submit an application to the Department of Revenue for tentative approval for
50 the tax credit in the year for which the tax credit is claimed or allowed. Applications shall be
51 accepted on a first come, first served basis. The Department of Revenue shall provide for the
Page 4 DRS45209-MGxfa-73A

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 manner in which the application is to be submitted and the information required in the application
2 which shall include, at a minimum, proof of the applicant business's out-of-pocket expenses. The
3 Department of Revenue shall review the application and tentatively shall approve the application
4 upon determining that it meets the requirements of this section by January 31 of the year after
5 the application was submitted. If the credit amounts on the tax credit applications filed with the
6 Department of Revenue exceed the maximum aggregate limit of tax credits, then the tax credit
7 must be allocated among the eligible business entities who filed a timely application on a first
8 come, first served basis based upon the amounts otherwise allowed by this section. Once the tax
9 credit application has been approved and the amount has been communicated to the applicant,
10 the eligible business then may apply the amount of the approved tax credit to its tax liability for
11 the tax year of which the approved application applies.
12 (f) Report. – By March 31 of each year, the Department of Revenue shall report to the
13 Joint Legislative Committee on Governmental Operations by county, the number of eligible
14 business tax credit applications the Department has received, the number of tax credit
15 applications approved, and the tax credits approved. This report must be made available in a
16 conspicuous place on the Department's website."
17 SECTION 4.1.(b) This section is effective for taxes imposed for taxable years
18 beginning on or after January 1, 2025.
