20 THRIVE AT MIDLIFE GRANT PROGRAM FOR SMALL BUSINESS
21 SECTION 4.2.(a) Creation; Administration. – The Thrive at Midlife Grant Program
22 (Program) is established and shall be administered by the Department of Health and Human
23 Services in accordance with this section.
24 SECTION 4.2.(b) Purpose. – The purpose of the program is to promote access to
25 and support for midlife healthcare by providing financial assistance in the form of grants to
26 eligible businesses who have out-of-pocket expenses.
27 SECTION 4.2.(c) Definitions. – The following definitions apply in this section:
28 (1) Department. – The Department of Health and Human Services.
29 (2) Eligible business. – A business with a physical presence in the State that (i)
30 has its headquarters located in this State, (ii) employs 50 or fewer people in
31 this State, (iii) has out-of-pocket expenses during the taxable year in which it
32 applies for grant funding under this section, and (iv) submits proof of its
33 out-of-pocket expenses on a form and in a manner approved by the
34 Department.
35 (3) Expenses for menopause treatment. – Expenses for any FDA approved
36 therapy, medication, or intervention prescribed by a licensed physician for
37 managing menopause symptoms, including the following:
38 a. Hormone replacement therapy.
39 b. Non-hormonal prescription treatments.
40 c. Prescription vaginal estrogen treatments.
41 (4) Expenses for midlife healthcare. – Expenses for any of the following:
42 a. Menopause related treatments, including hormone therapy,
43 prescription medications, and medically recommended non-hormonal
44 alternatives.
45 b. Preventative health screenings, including mammograms, cervical
46 cancer screenings, osteoporosis screenings, and cardiovascular risk
47 assessments.
48 c. Chronic disease management, including treatment of diabetes,
49 hypertension, cholesterol issues, and other midlife onset chronic
50 conditions.
DRS45209-MGxfa-73A Page 5

