9 MIDLIFE HEALTH ADVISORY COUNCIL
10 SECTION 7.2.(a) Article 1B of Chapter 130A of the General Statutes is amended
11 by adding new sections to read:
12 "§ 130A-33.45. Midlife Health Advisory Council; creation; duties; composition.
13 (a) There is established the Midlife Health Advisory Council in the Department. The
14 Council shall have the following duties and responsibilities:
15 (1) To make recommendations to the Governor and the Secretary aimed at
16 improving the health status of midlife women, defined as individuals residing
17 in North Carolina who were assigned female at birth or identify as women and
18 who are at least 40 but less than 65 years of age.
19 (2) To identify and examine the limitations and problems associated with existing
20 laws, regulations, programs, and services related to the health status of midlife
21 women.
22 (3) To examine the financing and access to health services for midlife women.
23 (4) To identify and review health promotion and disease prevention strategies
24 relating to the leading causes of death and disability among midlife women.
25 (5) To advise the Governor and the Secretary upon any matter which the
26 Governor or Secretary may refer to it.
27 "§ 130A-33.46. Midlife Health Advisory Council; members; selection; quorum;
28 compensation.
29 (a) The Midlife Health Advisory Council in the Department shall consist of 9 members,
30 to be appointed as follows:
31 (1) Five members shall be appointed by the Governor. Members appointed by the
32 Governor shall be representatives of the following groups: healthcare
33 professionals, public health experts, community advocates, and midlife
34 women with lived experience.
35 (2) Two members shall be appointed by the Speaker of the House of
36 Representatives, one of whom shall be a member of the House of
37 Representatives, and one of whom shall be a public member or a
38 representative of any of the groups specified in subdivision (1) of this
39 subsection.
40 (3) Two members shall be appointed by the President Pro Tempore of the Senate,
41 one of whom shall be a member of the Senate, and one of whom shall be a
42 public member or a representative of any of the groups specified in
43 subdivision (1) of this subsection.
44 (4) Of the members appointed by the Governor, two shall serve initial terms of
45 one year, two shall serve initial terms of two years, and one shall serve an
46 initial term of three years. Thereafter, the Governor's appointees shall serve
47 terms of four years.
48 (5) Of the nonlegislative members appointed by the Speaker of the House of
49 Representatives, one shall serve an initial term of two years. Thereafter,
50 nonlegislative members appointed by the Speaker of the House of
51 Representatives shall serve terms of four years. Of the nonlegislative members
DRS45209-MGxfa-73A Page 9

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 appointed by the President Pro Tempore of the Senate, one shall serve an
2 initial term of two years. Thereafter, nonlegislative members appointed by the
3 President Pro Tempore of the Senate shall serve terms of four years.
4 Legislative members of the Council shall serve two-year terms.
5 (b) The Chairperson of the Council shall be elected by the Council from among its
6 membership.
7 (c) The majority of the Council shall constitute a quorum for the transaction of business.
8 (d) Members of the Council shall receive per diem and necessary travel and subsistence
9 expenses in accordance with the provisions of G.S. 138-5 or G.S. 138-6, or travel and subsistence
10 expenses in accordance with the provisions of G.S. 120-3.1, as applicable.
11 (e) All clerical support and other services required by the Council shall be provided by
12 the Department."
13 SECTION 7.2.(b) There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department
14 of Health and Human Services the sum of two hundred fifty thousand dollars ($250,000) in
15 recurring funds for each year of the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium to be allocated to cover the
16 operating expenses of the Midlife Health Advisory Council authorized by subsection (a) of this
17 section.
